/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:33:The critique is right that tiny packets may miss the first genuine survivor and that conjugate completion alone is not enough; exact forced closure must be accounted for. But bounded small-family search is still a legitimate adversarial tactic, provided the claims are scoped correctly.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:66:- require exact closure of the simulated packet before simulation;
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:9:These three make the strongest portfolio because they cover the full mission risk surface without collapsing into one obstruction style. Chain 04 is the prerequisite gatekeeper: if the object is unstable or circular, later theorem work is fake. Chain 02 then attacks the inherited exact-NS non-isolability pressure in its most mission-aligned quantitative form, and it still pays off on failure because a vanishing-leakage family would become explicit anti-obstruction evidence. Chain 03 preserves the highest-upside adversarial route by directly trying to beat the obstruction with an exact small packet, so the portfolio does not overfit to one no-circuit narrative.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:23:Required to preserve a genuine negative-kill path. It is the highest-upside chain in the portfolio, and even on failure it returns a ranked failure atlas for small exact packets rather than an empty search narrative.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:5:The constructive search route is worth keeping, but only if it stops optimizing an ad hoc "Tao-likeness" surrogate and instead searches within a fixed exact admissibility framework. The goal is to find the smallest honest exact packet class that survives exact closure and still shows meaningful Tao-like delayed transfer behavior, or else to produce a bounded diagnostic atlas of why such small packets fail.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:11:- an explicit exact packet, with full forced-mode closure and tested dynamics, that provides serious anti-obstruction evidence within the searched class; or
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:12:- a bounded failure atlas for normalized small exact packet classes, listing the exact mechanisms that block Tao-like behavior under honest closure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:38:Action: for each family, expand the full forced closure honestly, not just conjugate completion, and record the resulting exact packet size.
