+
+## Operational Note
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The strategist launched
+  `codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-002`
+  through `bin/launch-role.sh` with sentinel
+  `explorations/exploration-002/REPORT-SUMMARY.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The session wrote only an initial report skeleton within the
+  bounded wait and did not produce the summary sentinel.
+- `[INFERRED]` This report is therefore completed directly from the anchored
+  local record.
+
+## Frozen Search Object
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The initial exact search object for this branch should be a
+  **finite helical mode support ledger**, not a packet-labeled family.
+  Concretely, Step 2 should enumerate finite sets
+
+  ```text
+  S subset { (k, sigma) : k in Z^3 \ {0}, sigma in {+, -} }
+  ```
+
+  modulo exact symmetries, with mandatory real-valued conjugate completion.
+- `[INFERRED]` Why helical rather than bare Fourier support:
+  the local record repeatedly treats helical sign data as structurally relevant
+  to exact coefficients, transfer sign, and phase bookkeeping.
+  Collapsing immediately to unlabeled Fourier supports would hide part of the
+  exact interaction law the mission is trying to test.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Why not packet-level search objects:
+  the predecessor mission's packet semantics were honest for its branch, but
+  this mission's Step 1 explicitly forbids smuggling desired-channel or
+  packet-sheet annotation into the raw object and defaults instead to finite
+  Fourier/helical supports unless a sharper alternative is justified.
+- `[INFERRED]` Allowed use of packet language:
+  predecessor-mission packets may still be used as seed templates or fixtures,
+  but only after translating them into explicit helical support ledgers.
+  They are not the primary search object.
+
+## Closure Convention
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Recursive exact closure is mandatory. Both the winning chain and
+  the attack/judgment record insist that first-generation companion accounting
+  is not enough.
+- `[INFERRED]` Frozen closure rule for a seed ledger `S_0`:
+  1. add every forced conjugate representative required by real-valuedness;
+  2. if two modes in the current ledger can participate in an exact helical
+     triad with nonzero coefficient, add the third mode and its conjugate;
+  3. include every helical sign sector that appears through the exact
+     coefficient law rather than by hand-pruning;
+  4. iterate until a fixed point `cl(S_0)` is reached or the ledger spills
+     outside the current budget.
+- `[INFERRED]` Leray-projection effects are part of the coefficient test, not a
+  later correction: Step 2 must decide triad forcing using the exact projected
+  interaction law, not a schematic graph.
+- `[INFERRED]` Repeated-mode identifications are part of the support ledger.
+  If closure causes two apparent channels to coincide as the same exact mode,
+  that counts as one mode with multiple interaction incidences, not as two
+  abstract packet slots.
+
+## Spectator Inclusion Rule
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Spectators belong in closure from the start. The attack and
+  judgment record makes this non-optional.
+- `[INFERRED]` Frozen policy:
+  every mode in `cl(S_0) \ S_0` is entered immediately in the support ledger as
+  a closure-forced spectator or companion mode.
+  The label `spectator` is descriptive only; it does not permit pruning the
+  mode out of the exact dynamics.
+- `[INFERRED]` Step 2 may record
+  `seed core`
+  versus
+  `closure-forced spectator ledger`
+  as a bookkeeping split, but both live inside the exact support object.
+
+## Admissible Enlargements
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Enlargement rule 1:
+  add one complete wavevector-helicity orbit
+  (together with its conjugate representative)
+  to the seed ledger, then rerun recursive exact closure.
+- `[INFERRED]` Enlargement rule 2:
+  add one complete exact triad orbit sharing at least one mode with the current
+  closed support, together with all symmetry partners required by conjugation
+  and triad relabeling, then rerun recursive exact closure.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Why an enlargement rule is required:
+  both the winning chain and the attack record warn that apparent locking or
+  frustration can be an artifact of over-pruning the finite encoding.
+- `[INFERRED]` Non-admissible moves:
+  changing the helical sign sheet,
+  switching to packet-level role labels,
+  dropping closure-forced spectators,
+  or altering the time window / thresholds are substantive model changes, not
+  enlargements.
+
+## Smallest-First Ordering
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Step 2 should enumerate seeds lexicographically by:
+  1. number of independent seed wavevector-helicity orbits up to conjugation;
+  2. shell span / geometric scale ratio needed to realize the seed;
+  3. dimension of the free geometric parameter family
+     (fewer continuous geometry knobs first).
+- `[INFERRED]` Within one seed budget, Step 2 should compare the resulting
+  fixed points by:
+  1. closed-support size after recursive closure;
+  2. number of exact active triad orbits in the closed support;
+  3. size of the closure-forced spectator ledger.
+- `[VERIFIED]` This ordering directly implements the planning criticism that
+  "smallest" must not be left informal.
+
+## Escalation Ladder
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Frozen initial ladder:
+  1. one exact triad orbit with mandatory conjugates and all exact helical-sign
+     sectors;
+  2. two-triad clusters sharing one exact mode;
+  3. three-triad clusters with one repeated wavevector across two scales;
+  4. then increase the seed orbit count by one and repeat the same closure and
+     enlargement audit.
+- `[INFERRED]` Negative conclusions before Step 5 remain class-limited:
+  failure at ladder level 1 or 2 kills only that budgeted support class, not
+  the broader mission.
+
+## Exploration Verdict
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Step 2 should enumerate finite helical supports with mandatory
+  conjugate completion and recursive exact closure.
+- `[INFERRED]` Packet families remain diagnostic seeds only.
+- `[INFERRED]` Spectator modes are part of the exact support ledger from the
+  first closure pass onward.
+- `[INFERRED]` The branch now has a concrete search object, closure rule,
+  admissible enlargement policy, smallest-first ordering, and escalation ladder
+  sharp enough for Step 2 to inherit.
+
+## Failed Attempts And Dead Ends
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The launched explorer did not finish a summary sentinel.
+- `[INFERRED]` Retaining the predecessor mission's packet object as the primary
+  search class was rejected because it would reintroduce role-labeled
+  canonicalization at the object-definition stage.

